not in this hack but i did write it at some point
turned out to be a bigger hassle than i wanted because guess what! half the time where it happens it's actually intended
i could, i don't think this uses any sprite tool
well, "intended" as in, the sprite table clear routine is supposed to not clear the load index
like for example in the sprite spawn code it sets the load index and THEN it calls the clear sprite table routine
because that makes sense
then for most instances where sprite ids change it's reinitialized by calling the sprite table clear routine, for example yoshi egg -> yoshi/1-up, or baby yoshi->adult yoshi
or winged goomba-> normal goomba, dhino rhino->dhino torch etc
so yeah, i had to manually go through ever single instance and determine whether or not it's intended there
so basically any instance where a new sprite slot is determined it cleared it and every time the sprite slot stayed the same i didn't
i'll release the patch with all the notes on which checks specifically for clarity though
